"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-26-paris-2024-olympics-super-falcons-will-bounce-back-from-brazil-defeat-enoh\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's sports minister, John Enoh has tipped the Super Falcons to bounce back from the defeat to Brazil.  Randy Waldrum's side started their campaign at the 2024 Olympic Games with a 1-0 loss to the Samba Girls at the Matmut Atlantique Stadium, Bordeaux on Thursday night.  Gabi Nunes scored the winning goal for Brazil eight minutes before the break.  Despite the defeat, Enoh is optimistic the Super Falcons will progress further in the women's football event.  \\\"Our hopes for this team is high. I leave here with strong hope that the Super Falcons can still qualify,\\\" Enoh said after the game.  The Super Falcons will lock horns with world champions Spain in their next game on Sunday.  EPL: Mikel Obi names two Chelsea players that dominate every team except Man City  England Job: Scholes identifies two managers who could replace Southgate  'I am upset, sad' - Neymar reacts after being dropped by Ancelotti from Brazil's squad  Real reason I did not include Neymar in Brazil squad - Ancelotti  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"